You would consider this good pizza only if you lack functioning taste buds. I ordered one plain slice and one pepperoni slice, as I consider myself a pizza connoisseur and use these two types of slices to gauge a pizza restaurant. If a pizza restaurant cannot make these two basic slices taste good, then it does not measure up to my expectations. Both slices were soggy and completely devoid of flavor. I should have judged this place by the "Grade Pending" sign on the door. I can only surmise that the brief review using the clichéd phrase "awesome" and the woefully misspelled review were written by either friends or family members of the owner.
